    "body": "### Problem\n\nIs it possible to implement functionality to:\n1. handle rpc connection error;\n2. reconnect, when connection was lost (rpc server restarted);\n\nCurrently I am using external rpc server:\n```\nvim.lsp.start( {\n    name = \"test\",\n    cmd = vim.lsp.rpc.connect( config.hostname, config.port ),\n    on_error = function ( e ) \n        vim.print( e )\n    end,\n} )\n```\n\nIf client is unable to connect - it just show error message, `on_error` callback is not called and client become unusable. No possibilily to try to connect again or handle this error. Only one way - is to restart nvim.\n\nSecond problem - if it was connected, but disconnect at some moment - is it possible to reconnect on nect request?\nCurrently behavior is the same as described above - client become unusable.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```\nvim.lsp.start( {\n    name = \"test\",\n    cmd = vim.lsp.rpc.connect( config.hostname, config.port ),\n    on_error = function ( e ) \n        vim.print( e )\n    end,\n} )\n```\n\nYou need external lsp server, listening at tcp socket.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPlease, see above.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nprivate server\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nall\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
